##  7. <a name='ReconciliationExecutionStatusNotification'></a>Reconciliation Execution Status Notification

###  7.1. <a name='ReconciliationSuccessfulExecutions'></a>Reconciliation Successful Executions

Disney will deliver a `....sucess.csv` file in in your /review/Reconciliation SFTP directory.
This file only contains a generic message

###  7.2. <a name='ReconciliationFailedExecutions'></a>Reconciliation Failed Executions

Disney will deliver a `....failure.csv` file in in your /review/Reconciliation SFTP directory.

* In case of invalid input files the failure file will contain a validation error message
* In case of internal processing errors the file will only contain a generic message

##  8. <a name='ReconciliationImportantNotes'></a>Reconciliation Important Notes

* `AsOf` timestamp included within the input filename: Every subscription should have an older or equal date than the AsOf value.
* An already integrated partner could see a second report, the audit report. DSS recommends moving to the new diff report, but the audit report will still be generated.
* DSS will compare subscriptions until Filename’s timestamp.
* Every omitted row in the input file will be considered a cancellation, if there's a difference reconciliation will produce a row into the diff-report.
